## 3. Schema State (as of 2026-04-28)

These tables are **implemented in `schema.sql`** using
`CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` and are considered the foundation.

### 3.1 `seasons`

Represents each basketball season.

- `id` INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT  
- `name` TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE  (e.g. `2025-26`)  
- `start_date` DATE NOT NULL  
- `end_date` DATE NOT NULL  
- `created_at` TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP  

### 3.2 `scheduled_games`

Represents the **official schedule**.

- `id` INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT  
- `season_id` INTEGER NOT NULL REFERENCES `seasons(id)`  
- `program_name` TEXT NOT NULL  (e.g. `Liberty`)  
- `gender` TEXT NOT NULL  (`boys` / `girls`)  
- `level` TEXT NOT NULL  (`varsity`, `jv`, `jr_high`)  
- `game_date` DATE NOT NULL  
- `game_time` TIME NOT NULL  
- `location_type` TEXT NOT NULL  (`home`, `away`, `neutral`)  
- `opponent_name` TEXT NOT NULL  
- `tournament_name` TEXT  
- `status` TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT `scheduled`
  (`scheduled`, `cancelled`, `rescheduled`, `completed`)  
- `notes` TEXT  
- `created_at` TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP  
- `updated_at` TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP  

### 3.3 `games`

Represents **actual game instances**, which may be linked to the
schedule or be standalone scouting games.

- `id` INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT  
- `scheduled_game_id` INTEGER REFERENCES `scheduled_games(id)`  (nullable)  
- `start_time` TIMESTAMP  
- `end_time` TIMESTAMP  
- `source_type` TEXT NOT NULL  (`pixellot`, `nfhs`, `manual`)  
- `source_key` TEXT NOT NULL  (NFHS ID, Pixellot ID, or file path)  
- `nfhs_game_id` TEXT  
- `nfhs_url` TEXT  
- `created_at` TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP  
- `updated_at` TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP  

### 3.4 `nfhs_matches`

Represents candidate and confirmed matches between scheduled games and
NFHS games.

- `id` INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT  
- `scheduled_game_id` INTEGER NOT NULL REFERENCES `scheduled_games(id)`  
- `nfhs_game_id` TEXT NOT NULL  
- `nfhs_url` TEXT NOT NULL  
- `match_status` TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT `candidate`
  (`candidate`, `confirmed`, `rejected`)  
- `confidence` REAL  
- `created_at` TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP  

### 3.5 `sources`

Allows multiple **video sources** per game.

- `id` INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT  
- `game_id` INTEGER NOT NULL REFERENCES `games(id)`  
- `source_type` TEXT NOT NULL  (`nfhs_vod`, `manual_upload`, `local_file`, etc.)  
- `source_path` TEXT NOT NULL  (file path or URL)  
- `created_at` TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP  
- `updated_at` TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP  

These 5 tables are **locked in** as the basis for schedule/game/film
features, alongside the pre-existing `events`, `analysis_runs`,
`detections`.

